<TITLE> M Muniruzzaman appointed new JU VC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (bdnews24.com)  Professor M Muniruzzaman of the department of physics has been appointed temporary vice chancellor of Jahangirnagar University, the education ministry said in a statement Monday. Professor Muniruzzaman is presently pro-vice chancellor of the university and will is set to also take on the post of vice chancellor for an unspecified time. According to the University Act 1973, the university senate normally elects a three-member panel from which the president then appoints a VC to a four-year term. JU acting registrar and senate secretary Kazi Mohiuddin said a senate meeting could not be convened on this occasion as the government did not give permission. The term of the immediate past VC Khandaker Mustahidur Rahman ended on Mar 20. Prof Muniruzzaman told bdnews24.com that he would take over his temporary post on Tuesday. He called on all to work collectively in the interests of the university. Muniruzzaman joined the university in 1972 as a lecturer. He was promoted to professor in 1989. He has held posts as president of the physics department, faculty dean and director of the Computer and Information Technology Institute. bdnews2
